## ⏱️ Key Points

* Centralized exception handling improves code cleanliness
* Custom exceptions make error handling more meaningful
* `ApiError` ensures consistent API responses
* Validation errors are handled separately with detailed messages

---

## ❗ Learnings

* Correct annotation is `@RestControllerAdvice` (not `@RestAdvices`)
* Always return appropriate HTTP status codes
* Validation errors should include all field-level messages
* Avoid handling exceptions inside controllers

---

## 🔑 Summary

👉 Global exception handling = cleaner controllers + better API responses
